# KapMan Trading Journal — Project Rules

## What this project is
A containerized Next.js trading journal that ingests thinkorswim broker CSVs,
runs FIFO lot matching, and displays a multi-screen analytics dashboard.

## Stack (pinned versions — do not deviate)
- Next.js 14.2.x with App Router
- TypeScript 5.4.x strict mode
- Tailwind CSS 3.4.x
- Prisma 5.14.x + PostgreSQL
- TanStack Table 8.17.x
- Recharts 2.12.x
- Zod 3.23.x
- Docker + docker-compose

## Architecture rules
- All DB access goes through Prisma only — no raw SQL
- All API route types shared via /types/api.ts
- Adapters only detect/parse/normalize — no FIFO or analytics logic inside adapters
- FIFO matching lives in /src/lib/ledger/ only
- Setup inference lives in /src/lib/analytics/ only

## File structure
- /src/app/ — Next.js App Router pages
- /src/lib/adapters/ — broker adapter registry
- /src/lib/ledger/ — FIFO engine
- /src/lib/analytics/ — setup classifier
- /types/api.ts — shared API contracts
- /fixtures/ — sample CSV files (use for all parser tests)
- /design/ — dashboard mock HTML (visual target)
- /docs/ — build spec and issues (read before generating code)

## Required environment variables
- DATABASE_URL
- NODE_ENV
- NEXT_TELEMETRY_DISABLED=1

A `.env.example` file must exist and match runtime requirements.

## Build order
1. Scaffold app shell, routes, Docker, Prisma schema, env template
2. Implement shared API contracts
3. Implement import/upload flow and persistence
4. Implement thinkorswim adapter parser
5. Implement executions table
6. Implement FIFO matching engine
7. Implement matched lots table
8. Implement setup inference and setups pages
9. Implement overview, TTS evidence, diagnostics
10. Add deployment config and health check

## Coding rules
- Named exports only — no default exports except Next.js page components
- Every page handles three states: loading, empty (with CTA), and populated
- No TODO comments unless the feature is in the Non-goals list in the build spec
- Every API route has a shared type in /types/api.ts
- List responses: { data, meta: { total, page, pageSize } }
- Detail responses: { data }
- Error responses: { error: { code, message, details[] } }

## CSV parsing rules (critical)
- The thinkorswim CSV has a leading empty column on every Trade History row
- Multi-leg spread rows have blank Exec Time on continuation legs
- Continuation legs may also have blank Order Type
- Net Price field may contain "DEBIT" or "CREDIT" — treat as non-numeric
- Price field may be "~" — treat as null, do not crash
- Spread types in real data: SINGLE, STOCK, VERTICAL, DIAGONAL, CALENDAR, COMBO, CUSTOM
- Unknown spread types must emit warnings, not be silently dropped
- Expirations do NOT appear in Account Trade History — infer from ledger only
- Account ID must be parsed from the first line of the file
- Fees are sourced from Cash Balance rows via REF #
- BAL rows populate daily_account_snapshots
- Emit one canonical execution per leg and assign shared spread_group_id for grouped spreads

## Multi-account rules
- The app must support multiple accounts
- Each uploaded CSV belongs to one account parsed from file metadata
- Imports, executions, matched lots, and setups must support account filtering

## Import workflow requirements
- Upload must show progress
- Show broker detection result before commit
- Show parse preview before commit
- Commit result must report parsed, persisted, and skipped rows
- Import history must show filename, broker, account, status, and row counts

## Diagnostics rules
- Synthetic expiration closes must be flagged as EXPIRATION_INFERRED
- Parser anomalies must surface on the Diagnostics page
- Tag inference failures must be counted as uncategorized
- Unknown spread types, COMBO, and CUSTOM rows must log warnings

## Definition of done
- `docker compose up` starts app and db successfully
- App is available at `http://localhost:3000`
- Prisma migrations run successfully
- Fixture data is seeded automatically in dev
- Parser tests pass against files in `/fixtures/`
- All nav pages render without runtime errors

## Off-limits
- No raw SQL
- No default exports on non-page files
- No TODO deferral of features that are in the build spec
- Do not merge spread legs inside the adapter
- Do not ask clarifying questions — make the conservative assumption and document it